{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(icon:accessibilityLabel:hierarchy:style:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(icon:text:hierarchy:style:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(text:hierarchy:style:action:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","generated":true},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/body"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"anchor":"Enumerations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/Hierarchy","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/Style"],"title":"Enumerations"},{"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/View-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Hierarchies","text":"Hierarchies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Four hierarchies are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}]},{"text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": The Strong “call for action” on the page should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"minimal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"negative","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Negative"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default hierarchy","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), hierarchy: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\")) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative hierarchy","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", hierarchy: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", hierarchy: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong hierarchy","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), text: \"Validate\", hierarchy: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Styles","text":"Styles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for following states disabled, pressed, hovered or normal (i.e. enabled)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"loading","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Colored-Surface","text":"Colored Surface"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If button is placed on colored surface using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrom.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative button on a colored surface.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/unified-design-system.orange.com\/472794e18\/p\/48a788-button"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"co